<T>__{cut back to:}
<L>__{interior salieri's apartment bedroom night 1780's}
<A>__{cu, the fireplace. in it lies the olivewood christ on the cross, burning.}
<C>__{old salieri }
<D>__{what use after all is man, if not to teach god his lessons?}
<A>__{the cross flames up and disintegrates. salieri stares at it.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<L>__{interior mozart's apartment living room night 1780's}
<A>__{the front door bursts open. mozart stumbles in, followed by emmanuel schikaneder, three young actresses, and another man, all fairly drunk. schikaneder (who appears everywhere accompanied by young girls) is a large, fleshy, extravagant man of about thirty five.}
<C>__{mozart}
<D>__{stanzi! stanzi! stanzi manzi!}
<A>__{the others laugh.}
<C>__{mozart}
<D>__{sssh!}
<C>__{schikaneder}
<P>__{(imitating mozart)}
<D>__{stanzi manzi banzi wanzi!}
<C>__{mozart}
<D>__{sssh! stay here.}
<A>__{he walks unsteadily to the bedroom door and opens it.}
<C>__{schikaneder}
<P>__{(to the girls, very tipsy)}
<D>__{sssh! you're dishgrashful!}
